LG.L:
With a visage pale, blue This seems to be taken out of Horace;
"Et tinctus violâ pallor amantium."
I hope the ghost of a Ballad-maker will not be offended with me for this discovery: I am sure the best French Poet now living reputes it an honour that it was said of him,
"N' est qu'un gueux revestu des depeuilles d' Horace.", and forlorn;
